1
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,100
Xu Xiao.

2
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,160
Eat more.

3
00:01:53,039 --> 00:01:54,640
Xu Xiao, you got into college.

4
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,900
I bought this new phone

5
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:56,759
for you.

6
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:00,380
No need.

7
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:01,560
Thank you.

8
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:03,440
No.

9
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,440
Your previous phone

10
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,520
is an old model.

11
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,639
I told your mom several times

12
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:09,699
to get you a new one.

13
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,000
Just take it.

14
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:14,380
I'll buy it myself if I need it.

15
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,840
Where does a college student like you get the money?

16
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:18,680
I checked.

17
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,680
The living expenses I sent to your bank card,

18
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,079
you haven't spent a cent.

19
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:23,420
I have a part-time job.

20
00:02:24,079 --> 00:02:25,340
I can make my own money.

21
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,620
Why are you being so stubborn?

22
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,240
You are grown up now.

23
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:31,240
Can't you be a little more sensible?

24
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:32,280
Also,

25
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,980
even if you refuse to call him Dad,

26
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,060
you could at least call him Uncle.

27
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,320
Well,

28
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,560
let the kid do whatever makes him comfortable.

29
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:44,079
He can call me whatever he wants.

30
00:02:44,079 --> 00:02:44,640
Besides,

31
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,520
he's grown up now.

32
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,160
He wants to support himself.

33
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:48,720
He's sensible.

34
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,720
It's a good thing.

35
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,120
Eat.

36
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,130
Have a piece of meat.

37
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,200
Eat more.

38
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,560
I have something to tell you.

39
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:04,600
Your uncle and I have discussed it.

40
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:06,400
You'll change your major in your sophomore year.

41
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,600
After you finish this semester,

42
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,130
we will apply to the school.

43
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,000
Why?

44
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:14,160
Your college entrance exam score was so high.

45
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:15,360
You had many choices.

46
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:18,520
Yet you insisted on choosing such an unpopular major.

47
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,200
You...

48
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,240
I like doing this.

49
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,520
Do you think our family hasn't suffered enough

50
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,450
because of this?

51
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,000
You are exactly like him,

52
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:35,930
always obsessed with those bottles and jars.

53
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,000
Xu Xiao,

54
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,079
I just don't understand.

55
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:41,020
You have such good grades.

56
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,520
Why didn't you choose a

57
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,760
promising major?

58
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:46,079
Why must you follow his ruined path?

59
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:48,640
He has grown up and has his own ideas.

60
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,329
I'm full.

61
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:51,850
I'm leaving.

62
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,220
Look at you.

63
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:56,120
I say a few words and he acts like this.

64
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,000
We're eating.

65
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,400
Eat properly.

66
00:04:39,159 --> 00:04:39,760
Class.

67
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,480
After the previous study,

68
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,180
everyone has mastered

69
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,020
the restoration techniques,

70
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:49,000
and acquired certain restoration skills.

71
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,080
Some students have long wanted to try

72
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,760
porcelain restoration.

73
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,560
In a while, the old neighbors

74
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,170
will bring their porcelain

75
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,090
to communicate with everyone.

76
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:58,880
Okay.

77
00:04:58,880 --> 00:04:59,440
Mr. Yue,

78
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:00,800
do you mean

79
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,240
we should collect all kinds of old porcelain here

80
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,560
and then restore them?

81
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,000
Yes.

82
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:08,360
I've already talked to the neighbors here.

83
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:10,320
They are all volunteering

84
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,920
to support our teaching practice activities.

85
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:13,840
But sir,

86
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,720
do they trust us?

87
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,040
Aren't they afraid that we novices

88
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:19,560
will ruin their porcelain during repair?

89
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,890
Don't worry about that.

90
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,920
Our old neighbors

91
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:25,000
trust our school very much.

92
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,920
Our Jingdezhen Ceramic University's

93
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,160
ceramic restoration in the Cultural Heritage Conservation major

94
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:28,960
What's wrong?

95
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,400
is very famous.

96
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:32,640
I'm just a little nervous.

97
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,600
I'm afraid I won't be able to restore the porcelain well again.

98
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,400
Be confident.

99
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:36,960
You have improved a lot.

100
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,200
Everyone should cherish the trust of the neighbors

101
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,730
and the honor of the school.

102
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,960
Come on, let's start getting ready.

103
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:42,520
Come on.

104
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:43,120
Go.

105
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:45,000
One group over here.

106
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:45,520
Okay.

107
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:46,400
Come.

108
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,120
Just this one.

109
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:47,650
Any more?

110
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:51,640
Young man.

111
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,300
Hello, sir.

112
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,130
Can this still be repaired?

113
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,040
Young man,

114
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,840
can you take a look

115
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,680
at my Kangxi wucai porcelain

116
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:01,280
and see if it can be fixed?

117
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,240
Wait a moment.

118
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:03,760
Sorry.

119
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,880
I think this item of yours

120
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,740
is an antique replica.

121
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,920
What nonsense are you talking about?

122
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,720
This is my family heirloom.

123
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,600
Kangxi official kiln wucai porcelain has regular shapes.

124
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:17,480
Yours looks more like a civilian kiln product.

125
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,760
The edge of the foot ring is pointed,

126
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,490
and there are missing patches.

127
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,960
What do you know?

128
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:26,360
You are just undergrads who haven't graduated.

129
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,440
If you don't know how to repair it,

130
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,120
forget it.

131
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,640
The body of official kiln porcelain is delicate,

132
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,570
white, and hard.

133
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,040
The glaze is smooth and lustrous.

134
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,159
The body and glaze are tightly combined.

135
00:06:33,159 --> 00:06:34,360
The patterns are exquisite,

136
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,760
and the inscriptions are neat.

137
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:36,600
As for yours,

138
00:06:37,159 --> 00:06:39,240
the body is rough, and the glaze is uneven.

139
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,500
The shape and patterns

140
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:41,840
do not match the era.

141
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,800
This young man makes sense.

142
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,080
This thing of yours

143
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,480
doesn't look authentic.

144
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,880
However, we don't do professional appraisals.

145
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,000
Authentic pieces and replicas,

146
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,060
we can repair both.

147
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,080
I won't repair it. I won't repair it.

148
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,280
If you're not repairing it, leave.

149
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:56,640
Here.

150
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:57,360
Young man,

151
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,040
what do you think of my cloud-dragon vase?

152
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,800
This is amazing.

153
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,640
It must be very valuable.

154
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:15,340
It's so beautiful.

155
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:21,840
Hello, ma'am.

156
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:22,200
Ma'am,

157
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:24,360
I heard you repair porcelain for free here.

158
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:26,280
Yes, we are from the Ceramic University.

159
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:28,610
Could you take a look at this teapot for me?

160
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:29,640
Okay.

161
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:32,520
Ma'am,

162
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,120
what era is this teapot from?

163
00:07:34,159 --> 00:07:35,480
I can't remember clearly.

164
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,240
It should be from the 60s.

165
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,280
Ma'am,

166
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:40,000
we restore cultural relics here.

167
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:40,880
This one

168
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,080
looks quite new.

169
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,680
There's probably no need to restore it.

170
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,040
Whether it's necessary to restore it,

171
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,500
is that up to you to decide?

172
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:49,960
If I had known you were so picky,

173
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,200
I wouldn't have come at all.

174
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,200
Ma'am, we really didn't mean that.

175
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,400
We didn't say we won't fix it.

176
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:53,880
Okay.

177
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:54,880
Ma'am, in three days,

178
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,600
right here,

179
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,060
you can come pick it up.

180
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:57,840
Okay.

181
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,680
Everyone now has porcelain

182
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:10,280
to be restored.

183
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,280
Please make sure to

184
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,040
handle it with care.

185
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,000
Restore it according to

186
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,920
the client's requirements.

187
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,400
We will return the restored items

188
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:21,760
in our next extracurricular practical class.

189
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:22,720
But I hope

190
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:23,920
your work

191
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,680
can be recognized by the clients.

192
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:32,679
My grandpa seems to have this kind of teapot too.

193
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,880
This thing is only worth a hundred bucks.

194
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,640
Why do I have to restore this?

195
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,440
The Jian tea bowl I need to restore,

196
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,919
with its color and texture,

197
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,520
is obviously very valuable.

198
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:42,679
What about yours?

199
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:46,080
Yuexin and I have a porcelain horse from the Qing Dynasty.

200
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:46,880
Look.

201
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,560
The one Xu Xiao and his team have

202
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:51,560
is a Wucai cloud and dragon vase from the Ming Dynasty.

203
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,760
Students,

204
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,480
in a moment, the neighbors

205
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,610
will come to collect

206
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:15,210
the porcelain they entrusted you to restore.

207
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,360
We will evaluate you

208
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:18,560
based on the satisfaction level of the restored porcelain.

209
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,680
I will grade you.

210
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,200
Get ready, everyone.

211
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,240
Come on.

212
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,200
Take a look.

213
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:24,840
It's okay.

214
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:25,760
Passable.

215
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,600
This is too sloppy.

216
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,880
How is it, miss?

217
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:29,760
Is it fixed?

218
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:30,440
You're here.

219
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:30,960
You're here.

220
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,960
This is what you brought in for repair.

221
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,600
Take a look.

222
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,120
This isn't glued well.

223
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:37,520
Let me try.

224
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,880
Aunt Wu, you're here.

225
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:39,520
Aunt Wu.

226
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,280
Is my item fixed?

227
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:41,920
It's done.

228
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:43,220
Take a look.

229
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:46,920
No.

230
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,280
This won't work.

231
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:50,000
Isn't it still usable?

232
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,480
Yeah.

233
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,240
It doesn't leak.

234
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,600
And you can still make tea with it.

235
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,680
You just glued it together.

236
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:56,040
How is this fixed?

237
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,100
It's worse than not fixing it.

238
00:09:58,280 --> 00:09:58,920
No, Aunt Wu.

239
00:09:58,920 --> 00:09:59,320
We...

240
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:01,240
This thing isn't worth much anyway.

241
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,920
Is that how you talk to your elders?

242
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:03,320
Auntie.

243
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,200
What are your names?

244
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,240
I'm going to see your teacher.

245
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:05,760
No, no.

246
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,690
You, come here. Both of you.

247
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,480
Calm down.

248
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:10,010
What's the problem?

249
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:10,800
Look.

250
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,600
Look at how they repaired it.

251
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,930
I just have one request.

252
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,160
Make it exactly like the original.

253
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:18,420
Aunt Wu's requirements are too high.

254
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,840
It can't be repaired at all.

255
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,480
We said back then we couldn't take the job.

256
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,160
I'll have them take it back and redo it.

257
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,560
Could you give the young people another chance?

258
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:26,090
Alright.

259
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,560
These young people nowadays, really...

260
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:29,280
Take care.

261
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:32,920
Mr. Liang.

262
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,570
How about I give it a try?

263
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,760
Teacher, let him do it.

264
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,090
It's so good to have you.

265
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:38,800
Xu Xiao,

266
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,880
are you sure you want to take over for them

267
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,000
and finish this restoration work?

268
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:42,520
He is sure.

269
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,050
I am sure.

270
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:58,800
Actually, I never quite understood

271
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,200
what kind of restoration

272
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,480
Aunt Wu really wants.

273
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:04,680
There are several kinds of restoration.

274
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,280
Some focus on usability.

275
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,760
Some focus on display.

276
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,900
And some incorporate artistic processing.

277
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:13,800
Lastly is the one we're familiar with:

278
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,530
cultural relic conservation.

279
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:18,080
Not everyone's purpose for restoration

280
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:18,840
is the same.

281
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,520
Does Aunt Wu think

282
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,720
filling the missing parts with plaster

283
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:24,760
is too ugly,

284
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:28,280
and completely different from what she imagined?

285
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,520
Then we'll try

286
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,540
working on the missing parts.

287
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,730
Restore it with porcelain pieces.

288
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:37,080
First, we'll use plaster

289
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,210
to make a prototype.

290
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,680
Then, use porcelain clay

291
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,940
to fire the fragments.

292
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:42,280
We just need to consider

293
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:45,010
the shrinkage rate of the fragments beforehand.

294
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:05,800
Cen.

295
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,240
You have a good eye for patterns.

296
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,600
I'll leave the drawing and coloring

297
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:11,360
to you.

298
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,200
Why do we have to

299
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,960
fire a new porcelain piece?

300
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,040
Couldn't we just use

301
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:30,040
the resin we learned in class

302
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:32,440
and ceramic filler to patch it up?

303
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:33,570
Wouldn't that work?

304
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,320
Aunt Wu's teapot pieces aren't complete.

305
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,580
It needs a large patch.

306
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:38,800
Besides,

307
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:41,160
Aunt Wu's teapot is a daily use item.

308
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,770
It will be used frequently.

309
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:43,880
So I decided to

310
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:46,000
use the porcelain-to-porcelain restoration method.

311
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,530
Porcelain-to-porcelain?

312
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:48,320
Yes.

313
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:50,320
This restoration method

314
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:52,440
is generally used on high-value items.

315
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:55,200
It means firing a piece identical to the original one,

316
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,360
matching the color and pattern.

317
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,320
After shaping and polishing, we add color.

318
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:01,320
Finally, we do the overall coloring and distressing.

319
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,800
I didn't know it was so complicated.

320
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,200
Since we accepted the commission,

321
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,400
we should do our best.

322
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,570
Let's begin.

323
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,040
When trimming,

324
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,040
we must be extremely focused.

325
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,760
And our hands must be steady.

326
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,000
Watch carefully.

327
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:25,300
Isn't this Xu Xiao?

328
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:26,410
Mr. Wang.

329
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:30,000
I'd like you to fire a piece of porcelain for me.

330
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,380
What do you need fired?

331
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,530
It's right here.

332
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:35,460
Have a look.

333
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:42,370
To fill a gap?

334
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:43,120
Yes.

335
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:44,360
All right.

336
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:46,120
I'm firing a batch of porcelain tonight.

337
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,920
You two can come pick it up tomorrow.

338
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:48,800
Thank you, Uncle Wang.

339
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:49,720
Thank you, Uncle Wang.

340
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:50,520
It's nothing.

341
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:53,200
Brother Hu,

342
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:56,290
thank you for helping me burn Xiaoqing last time.

343
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,120
Miss,

344
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,520
what are you talking about?

345
00:13:58,520 --> 00:13:59,650
I don't understand.

346
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,840
Miss,

347
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:06,000
isn't today the first time we've met?

348
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,600
You kid,

349
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,720
what did you do behind my back again?

350
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,400
Well, Uncle Wang,

351
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,160
we won't disturb you anymore.

352
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:14,420
We'll head back first.

353
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:16,480
See you tomorrow. Thank you, Uncle Wang.

354
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,240
It's fine.

355
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:18,900
Keep going.

356
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:21,080
Look, we changed a tool.

357
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:16,480
Here.

358
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:22,160
Hello.

359
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:24,040
Who are you?

360
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:24,800
Hello.

361
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:25,680
Well,

362
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:28,120
we are students from Jingdezhen Ceramic University,

363
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,880
majoring in cultural relic conservation.

364
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:31,740
In our previous practical class,

365
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:34,400
Auntie Wu entrusted us to help her restore her porcelain.

366
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,720
Here, have some water.

367
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:36,720
Thank you.

368
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Good thing I came back to get something today.

369
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,800
Otherwise, you would have made a trip for nothing.

370
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,240
Does Mrs. Wu usually live here alone?

371
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,860
This is my family's old house.

372
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,480
After my grandfather passed away,

373
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,010
I got married and moved out.

374
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:53,570
Now my mom lives here alone.

375
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,640
What did my mom ask you to repair?

376
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:02,480
This teapot,

377
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:03,800
I remember it.

378
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:05,960
When I was cleaning the room last month,

379
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:07,360
I accidentally broke it.

380
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,800
But I remember throwing it in the trash.

381
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:11,400
Why did she take it out again?

382
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:14,100
Aunt Wu seems to care a lot about this teapot.

383
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:15,840
But my mom doesn't usually drink tea.

384
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,300
I've never seen her use it.

385
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:20,040
She didn't give you a hard time, did she?

386
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:24,120
My mom's temper has been getting worse these past few years.

387
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,360
Now when I come home to see her,

388
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,960
she loses her temper with me.

389
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:32,440
Mrs. Wu.

390
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,460
Why did you come to my home?

391
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:37,640
Mrs. Wu,

392
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,240
we've fixed your teapot.

393
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,800
The broken part

394
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:48,720
has been refired.

395
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:51,400
There are also signs of use.

396
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,440
We also kept it.

397
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:04,079
If the teapot is broken, so be it.

398
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,680
I can just buy you a new one.

399
00:17:06,119 --> 00:17:08,280
Why did you pick it out of the trash?

400
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:11,800
Mom.

401
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,680
At least say something.

402
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,920
These two students have been waiting for you for a long time.

403
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,450
You're the only polite one.

404
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:18,480
Besides,

405
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:19,880
they volunteered.

406
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,680
I didn't beg them to do it.

407
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:23,920
Mom, how can you say that?

408
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:25,599
We should at least thank them.

409
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,240
Aunt Wu,

410
00:17:28,359 --> 00:17:31,160
Are you unsatisfied with our restoration?

411
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:34,840
Does it even matter if I'm satisfied or not?

412
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:37,290
It's fine as long as you're satisfied.

413
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:42,800
I'm really sorry.

414
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:44,770
My mom just has this temper.

415
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:46,540
Please don't take it to heart.

416
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:47,440
It seems Aunt Wu

417
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,770
still feels we didn't do a good enough job.

418
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:51,320
Not exactly.

419
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:52,760
Can we take

420
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,730
this teapot back again?

421
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:56,960
Of course.

422
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,720
I really don't understand

423
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:10,520
what Aunt Wu wants.

424
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,530
There must be something we missed.

425
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:34,560
Boss,

426
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,050
how much is this?

427
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,000
Handsome.

428
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:40,400
Handsome!

429
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:42,000
Coming,

430
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,000
customer.

431
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:44,480
You called for handsome, right?

432
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:45,400
I'm coming.

433
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:46,040
No.

434
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:47,680
Why is he ignoring me?

435
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:48,640
He ignores you,

436
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:49,440
but I'm not.

437
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:50,160
What's up?

438
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:50,800
Buying or selling?

439
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:51,880
Is he your clerk?

440
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:52,480
Of course.

441
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,840
You hire clerks like this?

442
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:55,100
None of your business.

443
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:56,940
I'm not in the mood. Forget it.

444
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,920
Does Aunt Wu usually live here alone?

445
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,800
This is my family's old house.

446
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:04,120
After my grandfather passed away,

447
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:06,050
I also moved out when I got married.

448
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:16,960
But my mom doesn't usually drink tea.

449
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,360
I haven't seen her use it.

450
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:21,640
Look at how they repaired it.

451
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:22,970
I only have one request.

452
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:25,240
Just fix it exactly as it was.

453
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:32,760
Xiaocen.

454
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:36,060
Send me the photo of the teapot before it was broken.

455
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:52,240
Hello.

456
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,240
Are you at home?

457
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,170
I am downstairs.

458
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,680
Bring the teapot with you now.

459
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,340
I'll wait for you downstairs.

460
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:07,040
Mom, I'm going out for a bit.

461
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,200
Going out so late?

462
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:08,600
Yes.

463
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,440
Did you bring the pot?

464
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:13,170
I brought it.

465
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,160
I think

466
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:16,220
I know why Aunt Wu is angry.

467
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:17,840
Let's go.

468
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:18,570
Come with me.

469
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:36,120
I'm really sorry.

470
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,970
My mom just has this temper.

471
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:39,620
Sorry for the trouble.

472
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:40,680
It's fine.

473
00:20:41,520 --> 00:20:42,320
I understand.

474
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:55,800
Mrs. Wu.

475
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:57,720
I am so sorry.

476
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,620
We are not skilled enough.

477
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:03,160
We can't do a seamless repair

478
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:05,500
and restore it to its original state.

479
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:08,120
We have tried our best to restore it

480
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:09,920
to the way you are familiar with.

481
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:12,500
I just hope you can take a look.

482
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:04,680
There, there. Don't cry.

483
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:06,600
It's just a bump.

484
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,680
It's not a big deal.

485
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,560
I will show you a magic trick later.

486
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:12,200
Okay?

487
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:13,480
Come here.

488
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,920
Let Daddy show you a magic trick.

489
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,360
Here.

490
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,400
A small gap.

491
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:31,760
Abracadabra.

492
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:36,920
Look.

493
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:39,120
Didn't it turn into the character 'Wu'?

494
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:39,840
Right?

495
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:42,300
It's fixed.

496
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,360
Now it's fixed, right?

497
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:55,100
It's fixed.

498
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:07,720
It's okay, Mom.

499
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:15,160
Thank you.

500
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:21,660
All right, Mom.

501
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:23,120
Don't be sad.

502
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:27,960
It's all in the past, Mom.

503
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,600
Xu Xiao,

504
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:41,810
you're really amazing.

505
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,840
How did you figure out

506
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:46,170
there was a secret at the bottom of the pot?

507
00:23:46,720 --> 00:23:47,440
Actually,

508
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,130
when I first started repairing it,

509
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:53,120
I already saw the marks on the bottom of the pot.

510
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:56,560
At the time, I also thought they were just ordinary scratches.

511
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,290
Later, on the wall of her house,

512
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:00,890
I saw Mr. Wu's handwriting.

513
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:02,560
I thought

514
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:04,250
Aunt Wu's father

515
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:07,000
must be a playful person.

516
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:10,700
Thank you for helping Aunt Wu get back

517
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,300
such beautiful memories.

518
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,020
We did it together.

519
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:22,560
Actually, I was thinking

520
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:25,560
the reason why Aunt Wu was so angry

521
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:28,160
is because this porcelain

522
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:31,300
carries all the moments she shared with her family.

523
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,920
But this beautiful affection

524
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:35,640
seems to be fading away.

525
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:37,640
I think

526
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:40,720
the opposite of life is not death,

527
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:42,840
but being forgotten.

528
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:44,680
So I feel that

529
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:46,640
we are not just helping them

530
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,880
restore porcelain.

531
00:24:48,280 --> 00:24:49,340
More importantly,

532
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:52,280
we are restoring the beauty

533
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:54,050
and memories behind it.

534
00:24:58,160 --> 00:24:59,820
We only live for a few decades,

535
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:02,570
but we can spar with infinite time.

536
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,280
Isn't that interesting?
